Indian AI firms pledge GPUs as collateral for loans
GPU-backed loans help unlock capital without equity dilution
GPU financing in India is nascent but demand is rising rapidly

As India's AI infrastructure buildout and related services gather pace, GPUs (Graphics processing unit) are becoming the new asset class for raising debt among data centres, neocloud providers and AI startups
Popular in the US, where firms such as CoreWeave, Lambda and Crusoe have tapped GPU-backed financing, the model is now finding early traction in India with companies like Yotta and Neysa.
